# GameServices — root ignores for the web-service half of the repo (the shared
# nginx/TLS engine + the services behind it). DayZ-Server/ keeps its own
# .gitignore. Per-subproject .gitignore files also exist (StaticishSite/,
# Api/app/); this root file is the single place for host-level secrets and
# cross-cutting generated output. Committable *.example siblings stay tracked.

# ── Secrets / machine-specific (never commit; ship a *.example.env/.json instead) ──
# Per-env host configs (host.config.prod.env / host.config.staging.env; legacy bare
# host.config.env). The negation keeps the tracked example.
/host.config.env
/host.config.*.env
!/host.config.example.env
**/deploy/deploy.config.json
**/secrets.env
# Bruno collection credentials (Api/bruno/.env — .env.example stays tracked)
**/.env
**/customView.bru

# ── Rendered runtime config (generated from *.template) ──
**/config.json

# ── Deploy artifacts (regenerated every run) ──
**/deploy/stage/
**/logs/
*.log

# ── Node (Webhooks app) ──
**/node_modules/
**/dist/

# ── Hugo (StaticishSite) ──
/StaticishSite/public/
/StaticishSite/resources/
/StaticishSite/.hugo_build.lock
/StaticishSite/bin/

# ── Config Viewer (vendored Swagger UI, provisioned by Deploy-ConfigViewer.ps1) ──
/ConfigViewer/web/vendor/
# Map tile pyramids + browser height grids — derived artifacts rendered by
# DayZHeightmap/Build-MapTiles.ps1 -Execute -Deliver
/ConfigViewer/web/tiles/

# ── Monitoring — vendored Node Exporter Full dashboard (fetched pinned by Deploy-Monitoring.ps1) ──
/Monitoring/deploy/vendor/

# ── Api — OpenAPI spec generated from code (src/spec.ts via `npm run spec`) ──
/Api/openapi.json

# ── Editor / OS / agent cruft ──
.claude/
CLAUDE.md
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
